            <hgroup>
                <h2>Location and time advice</h2>
                <h3>By John | January 7, 2025</h3>
            </hgroup>
            <p>At first, I thought Uber was helping me make more money by showing me where I could find more gigs....
            </p>
            <ol>
                </p>I would get notifications with location advice, which initially seemed innocent. However, I quickly
                    noticed that when I arrived at the suggested locations, business wasn’t necessarily better.</p>
                </p>That’s not all. As a father of three, I used to work mostly on weekdays, which allowed me to spend
                    weekends with my kids. But a few weeks ago, Uber announced that drivers who work on Fridays,
                    Saturdays, and Sundays earn 85% more than those who work during the week. This revelation led me to
                    change my schedule to work more on weekends.</p>
                
                </p>On one hand, I’m grateful for this insight because I want to support my family financially as much
                    as possible. On the other hand, I’m spending less time with my kids and often feel too exhausted to
                    be the engaged father I want to be when I’m home.</p>
                
                </p>I’m left wondering how Uber determines these time and location recommendations. Are they truly
                    designed to benefit drivers, or do they primarily serve Uber’s interests? More importantly, are
                    these notifications ethically responsible and compliant with regulations?</p>
                
                </p>I would appreciate any insights into this, as I’m unsure of what to do moving forward.</p>
                
                </p>Thank you in advance for your help!</p>
                
                </p>Kind regards,</p>
                
                </p>John</p>
                

            </ol>
        </article>

